cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with policy gradient methods for reinforcement learning with function approximation. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as reinforcement learning is often used in robotics. It could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as reinforcement learning is used in control systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as function approximation is often done using neural networks.
